{"lemma":"قُنُوتُ","slug":"قُنُوتُ","root":"ق.ن.ت","root_slug":"ق-ن-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ن-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36272","n36275"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36272","headword_ar":"قُنُوتٌ","root":"qnt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanata","text_ar":"قَنَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being obedient:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, MA, Mgh, K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being constantly obedient:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, O, TA:) the former is the primary meaning: and hence, in the Kur [xxxiii. 35], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@loqaAnitaAti","text_ar":"وَا@لْقَانِتَاتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@loqaAnitiyna","text_ar":"وَا@لْقَانِتِينَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the obedient men and the obedient women"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanata lil~`hi","text_ar":"قَنَتَ لِلّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanata A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قَنَتَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [but this latter is unusual, the former only being authorized by the Kur-án (in iii. 38 and xxxiii. 31),] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was obedient to God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, TA.) And it is said in the Kur [ii. 110 and xxx. 25], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~N lahu qaAnituwna","text_ar":"كُلٌّ لَهُ قَانِتُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"All are obedient unto Him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the meaning here is, that the beings in heaven [and earth] are created by the will of God, and that none of them can alter the form in which it is created; the obedience here spoken of being obedience to the will [of God], not the obedience of religious service; some of them being obedient [in this sense], and others being disobedient. (L, TA.) [It is said that] the proper signification of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaAnitu","text_ar":"القَانِتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or the signification that implies all the meanings of the word] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The performer of the command of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) ―         -b2-  It signifies also The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA;) mentioned by Th, and asserted by him to be the primary meaning. (TA.) And (TA) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standing long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, O, TA.) And (TA) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standing in the performance of the divinely-appointed act of prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA.) [See also 4.] Hence, (Mgh, Msb, TA,) it is said in a trad. (S, TA) of the Prophet, as a reply given by him to the question"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u AlS~alaApi","text_ar":"اَىُّ الصَّلَاةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoDalu","text_ar":"اَفْضَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoDalu AlS~alaApi Tuwlu Alqunuwti","text_ar":"اَفْضَلُ الصَّلَاةِ طُولُ القُنُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, TA) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most excellent characteristic of the performance of the divinely-appointed act of prayer is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the long continuance of the standing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, * Msb, * TA.) And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunuwtu Alwitori","text_ar":"قُنُوتُ الوِتْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S; [see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wtr","text_ar":"وتر"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) or [as it is also termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duEaA='u","text_ar":"دُعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqunuwti","text_ar":"القُنُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The supplication of the standing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) for one utters the supplication standing: (TA:) and what is thus termed ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duEaA='u","text_ar":"دُعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqunuwti","text_ar":"القُنُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is as follows:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~ahum~a A_in~aA nasotaEiynuka wanasotagofiruka","text_ar":"اَللَّهُمَّ اـِنَّا نَسْتَعِينُكَ وَنَسْتَغْفِرُكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wanuw^ominu bika wanatawak~alu Ealayoka wanuvoniY Ealayoka Alxayora walaA","text_ar":"وَنُوْمِنُ بِكَ وَنَتَوَكَّلُ عَلَيْكَ وَنُثْنِى عَلَيْكَ الخَيْرَ وَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakofuruka wanaxolaEu wanatoruku mano yafojuruka Aall~`hum~a A_iy~aAka naEobudu","text_ar":"نَكْفُرُكَ وَنَخْلَعُ وَنَتْرُكُ مَنْ يَفْجُرُكَ اَللّٰهُمَّ اـِيَّاكَ نَعْبُدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaka nuSal~iY wanasojudu waA_ilayoka nasoEaY wanaHofidu narojuw raHomataka","text_ar":"وَلَكَ نُصَلِّى وَنَسْجُدُ وَاـِلَيْكَ نَسْعَى وَنَحْفِدُ نَرْجُو رَحْمَتَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wanaxo$aY Ea*aAbaka A_in~a Ea*aAbaka biAlkuf~aAri muloHiqN","text_ar":"وَنَخْشَى عَذَابَكَ اـِنَّ عَذَابَكَ بِالكُفَّارِ مُلْحِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, verily we beg of Thee aid"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be obedient and to forsake disobedience,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and we beg of Thee forgiveness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sins, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and we believe in Thee, and we rely"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2567},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon Thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and we laud Thee well, and we will not be unthankful to Thee for Thy favour, and we cast off and forsake him who disobeys Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, Thee we worship, and to Thee we perform the divinely-appointed act of prayer, and prostrate ourselves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and we are quick in working for Thee and in serving Thee: we hope for Thy mercy, and we dread Thy punishment: verily Thy punishment overtakes the unbelievers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus this clause is expl. on the authority of Ks: or, as some say, it means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causes"},{"kind":"text","text":"others"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to overtake,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become associated with, the unbelievers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lHq","text_ar":"لحق"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) It is said of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanata $ahorFA","text_ar":"قَنَتَ شَهْرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY SalaApi AlS~uboHi baEoda Alr~ukuwEi yadoEuw EalaY riEolK wa*akuwaAna","text_ar":"فِى صَلَاةِ الصُّبْحِ بَعْدَ الرُّكُوعِ يَدْعُو عَلَى رِعْلٍ وَذَكُوَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stood during a month, in the prayer of daybreak, after"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the prayers of)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwE","text_ar":"رُكُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"(pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakaEa","text_ar":"رَكَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cursing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the tribes of)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rial and Dhekwán"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplicating"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Zj, Mgh, O, Msb, K, TA:) this is the signification [most] commonly known. (Zj, Mgh, O, TA.) And [particularly, accord. to general usage,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplicating God"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by addressing Him with the form of words mentioned above as used in what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duEaA='u Alqunuwti","text_ar":"دُعَا=ءُ القُنُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doing so standing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divinely-appointed act of prayer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaApN","text_ar":"صَلَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAmb, O, TA.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being silent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, K, TA;) by which is meant (O, * TA) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withholding oneself from talking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, * K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaAp","text_ar":"الصَّلَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, * Msb, TA.) Hence, (O, Msb, TA,) accord. to a trad., (O, TA,) the saying in the Kur [ii. 239],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waquwmuwA","text_ar":"وَقُومُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lil~`hi qaAnitiyna","text_ar":"لِلّٰهِ قَانِتِينَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And stand ye unto God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the divinely-appointed act of prayer,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refraining from talking"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, Msb, TA.) ―         -b6-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serving of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuing of the performance of the pilgrimage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanata","text_ar":"قَنَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aqnt","text_ar":"اقنت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He continued the performance of the pilgrimage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K, TA.) ―         -b8-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prolonging of engaging in warring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warring and plundering."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanata","text_ar":"قَنَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aqnt","text_ar":"اقنت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prolonged the engaging in warring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warring and plundering."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K, TA.) ―         -b9-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confessing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acknowledging, one's being in the condition of a servant"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b10-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeping to obedience"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with lowliness, humility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissiveness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanata lahu","text_ar":"قَنَتَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive, to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanatati AlmrAp lizawojihaA","text_ar":"قَنَتَتِ المراة لِزَوْجِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaEolihaA","text_ar":"لِبَعْلِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive, and obedient, to her husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, quiet and submissive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqar~at","text_ar":"اَقَرَّت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also 4, and 8.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanaAtapN","text_ar":"قَنَاتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is an inf. n., of which the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanuta","text_ar":"قَنُتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatuna","text_ar":"قَتُنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eating little"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qataAnapN","text_ar":"قَتَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","Msb","S","M","Mgh","K","TA","IAmb","O","Zj","A"]},{"entry_id":"n36275","headword_ar":"قَنُوتٌ","root":"qnt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive, and obedient"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to her husband]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}